Import/export custom Pokédex CSV files to see coverage for different Pokémon. Create a custom CSV file with just the OU tier Pokémon, or even create your own Pokémon from scratch.
CSV data is loaded by column header name, not column order, so you can add or re-order columns if you want (e.g. add a “tier” column, or a “notes” column).
CSV files can be edited with Google Sheets, Microsoft Excel, OpenOffice, LibreOffice, Notepad, and more.
Export the default Pokédex to a CSV file
Import an edited Pokédex CSV file
Imported {{ n }} Pokémon forms from “{{ file }}”
Error loading CSV. Don't change header names.
Search by name, number, or types
You can search for a Pokémon by name. If you only remember part of the Pokémon's name, It can still probably find it for you. It can't deal with typos right now though.
Search by national dex number. If you want Bulbsaur, just type 1, not #001.
Here are a few examples of how to seach by type.
Search for Pokémon that have a fire as either of their types in any form (e.g. Charmander, Charizard, Rotom).
Search for Pokémon that are either water/flying (e.g. Gyarados) or flying/water (e.g. Cramorant).
Search for Pokémon that are only grass type, no 2nd type (e.g. Tangela, Chikorita, Lilligant).
